results.name: Decimal expansion of square root of 35.
comment: Continued fraction expansion is 5 followed by {1, 10} repeated. - _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 04 2009

This is the length of the long leg of a right triangle with hypotenuse 6 and small leg 1. So this is half the length of the longest line segment that can be drawn within a circular ring with radii 6 and 1. - _Michel Marcus_, Jun 20 2020
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
program: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20080); x=sqrt(35); for (n=1, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b010490.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Jun 04 2009
xref: Cf. A040029 (continued fraction), A010606 (cube root of 35).
